Package org.jconfigurations.converters

Contains the ConfigurationConverter interface and its implementations.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CollectionConfigurationConverter<T>
    CollectionConfigurationConverters are used by configurators to convert a configuration value into an instance of a Collection of type T.
    ConfigurationConverter<T>
    ConfigurationConverters are used by configurators to convert a configuration value into an instance of type T.
    MapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
    MapConfigurationConverters are used by configurators to convert a configuration value into an instance of a Map of types K and V.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BaseCollectionConfigurationConverter<T>
    Handy abstract class that implementations of CollectionConfigurationConverter can extend.
    BaseMapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
    Handy abstract class that implementations of MapConfigurationConverter can extend.
    BigDecimalConfigurationConverter  
    BigIntegerConfigurationConverter  
    BooleanConfigurationConverter  
    DoubleConfigurationConverter  
    FileConfigurationConverter  
    FloatConfigurationConverter  
    HashMapConfigurationConverter<K,V>
    A MapConfigurationConverter that converts a string value into an initialized HashMap.
    IntegerConfigurationConverter  
    ListConfigurationConverter<T>
    A CollectionConfigurationConverter that converts a string value into an initialized ArrayList.
    LongConfigurationConverter  
    NoCollectionConfigurationConverter
    Special CollectionConfigurationConverter that always throws a ConfigurationException when its NoCollectionConfigurationConverter.convert(java.lang.String) method is called.
    NoConfigurationConverter
    Special ConfigurationConverter that always throws a ConfigurationException when its NoConfigurationConverter.convert(java.lang.String) method is called.
    NoMapConfigurationConverter
    Special MapConfigurationConverter that always throws a ConfigurationException when its NoMapConfigurationConverter.convert(java.lang.String) method is called.
    SetConfigurationConverter<T>
    A CollectionConfigurationConverter that converts a string value into an initialized HashSet.
    StringConfigurationConverter  
    URLConfigurationConverter  

Package org.jconfigurations.converters Description

 Contains the ConfigurationConverter interface and its implementations.
